### Test Semantic Cache Demo
### Make sure you have uploaded a document first!

### 1. Get initial cache stats
GET http://localhost:3001/query/cache/stats

###

### 2. First query (cache miss - will call OpenAI)
POST http://localhost:3001/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "What is artificial intelligence?",
  "topK": 5
}

###

### 3. Exact same query (exact match cache hit)
POST http://localhost:3001/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "What is artificial intelligence?",
  "topK": 5
}

###

### 4. Paraphrased query (semantic match cache hit)
POST http://localhost:3001/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Can you explain what AI is?",
  "topK": 5
}

###

### 5. Check cache stats after queries
GET http://localhost:3001/query/cache/stats

###

### 6. Clear cache
POST http://localhost:3001/query/cache/clear

###

### 7. Verify cache is cleared
GET http://localhost:3001/query/cache/stats
